Thailand's Rattanapol Sor Vorapin retained his  International Boxing Federation straw-weight title on Saturday after knocking  out challenger Roger Espanola.
Rattanapol floored the ninth-ranked Filipino in the sixth round of the  scheduled 12-round bout in the central Thai province of Saraburi.
In his sixth title defence, Rattanapol dominated the fight from the start  with strong left and right hooks to the body and face, while Espanoya managed  only occasional right hooks and light left jabs to his opponent's face.
Rattanapol improved his fight record to 18 wins, including 13 knockouts,  one draw and two losses. Espanola's record now stands at 15 wins, including 10  knockouts, one draw and two losses.
